title: Did Biden, Ossoff, and Warnock Mislead Public With Promise of ‘$2000 Checks’?
subtitle: The fact that $600 plus $1,400 equals $2,000 is relevant here.
author: Alex Kasprak
vclaim: In late December 2020 and early January 2021, President-elect Joe Biden and Georgia U.S. Senate candidates Jon Ossoff and Raphael Warnock misled the public with claims that winning both Georgia races would allow the immediate passage of "$2,000 checks" for COVID-19 relief.
